course_title: Empirical Methods for Food and Resource Economics

sections.comments: The instructor will also accept FRST 231 or EPSE 482 towards the statistic prerequisite for this course. For non-LFS students, the instructor will also accept ECON 325. If you present with one of these courses, please email students@landfood.ubc.ca for registration assistance.

description: Introduction to empirical methods with applications for problems in food and resource economics; standard linear regression and methods to address data deficiencies; interpretation of regression results for forecasting and policy analysis.
